Responding to reports that $3 billion in Iranian funds would be unfrozen, a U.S. official tells the Jerusalem Post:

"No frozen funds have been released and no frozen funds will be released unless Iran meets the requirements outlined in the MOU. As the MOU outlines, the United States must approve how the funds are used. If Iranian assets are released, they will be used to purchase American agricultural products from American farmers to feed the Iranian people."
